{
  "text": "The actual values of the coefficients in linear equations for tensile strength and initial modulus (Eqs. [CITATION_1] and (14)) are presented in section \"Data processing results\", together with other results. For allowable strain the Gaussian regression curve is accepted, in the following form: There is no standard form for mathematical description of the ultimate strain curves for different propellant compositions based on HTPB polymer. The Gaussian curve is just an example for an appropriate regression function.",
